page.title: 18ECOLOGY OF SWINFORD
page.content: {Birds}on The{Stanford Reservoir. Grebes, geese, mallard, tufted and ruddy duck, moorhen, coot, common sandpiper, lapwing, gulls, shoveler, wigeon, pochard, swans, reedbunting, grey heron, tawny and little owl, red wagtail, skylark, kestrel, hobby, sparrowhawk and kingfisher. {Trees}- most common is the ash, followed by horse chestnut, sycamore, oak, field maple, elm, elder, willow, hazel, whitebeam, larch,(1 only) and holly (few). {Wild flowers}one June weekend numbered 30 varieties - bogstitchwort,plantain, bryony,bugle,buttercup,campion,sorrel, chickweed,cinquefoil,cleavers,ragwort, clover,cowparsley,daisy,dandelion,dock deadnettle,foxglove,forget me not,ivy, garlicmustard,ground elder,heartsease, speedwell,hedge parsley,herb robert, stitchwort,mallow and pineapple weed.
